You’re Trapnest’s guitarist.

27
00:04:34.732 --> 00:04:36.776 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Flowers wither after a little time anyway,

28
00:04:36.859 --> 00:04:40.405 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so I’m making good use of them
while they still have value.

29
00:04:40.488 --> 00:04:42.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not a story I prefer.

30
00:04:42.949 --> 00:04:45.618 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But you won’t wither, Ren!

31
00:04:50.415 --> 00:04:52.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
In any case, look at this gorgeous room.

32
00:04:52.750 --> 00:04:54.460 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And you each get a room to yourself?

33
00:04:54.544 --> 00:04:57.171 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is what they call
a "Suite Room," right?

34
00:04:57.255 --> 00:05:00.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nope. "Deluxe Room."

35
00:05:01.759 --> 00:05:04.304 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s deluxe, all right,
especially this bath.

36
00:05:04.387 --> 00:05:07.515 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s unnecessarily too big.
I don’t feel comfortable.

37
00:05:09.767 --> 00:05:13.146 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Being here like this is
like going back in time.

38
00:05:13.229 --> 00:05:15.857 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We used to soak in the bathtub
every day like this

39
00:05:15.940 --> 00:05:17.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and talk about all kinds of stuff.

40
00:05:18.651 --> 00:05:23.531 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The bathroom in our room was small,
but it was comfortable, and I liked it.

41
00:05:24.198 --> 00:05:26.951 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Say, Ren, what are we gonna do
about that room?

42
00:05:27.035 --> 00:05:29.787 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Nobody’s living there, so it’s a waste.
You should clear it out.

43
00:05:29.871 --> 00:05:33.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s okay. That was my starting point.

44
00:05:33.916 --> 00:05:36.711 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
One day, I’ll buy it,
return in my old age,

45
00:05:36.794 --> 00:05:39.422 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and quietly live there together with you.

46
00:05:40.423 --> 00:05:42.800 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don’t make decisions for me
about when I get old.

47
00:05:42.884 --> 00:05:47.388 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When I was a kid,
that building was used for storage.

48
00:05:47.472 --> 00:05:50.808 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I would run away from that
shitty orphanage and go hide there.

49
00:05:50.892 --> 00:05:54.896 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I found a guitar and made it my own,
and I would play it there all night.

50
00:05:55.563 --> 00:05:58.941 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Regardless of whether you were born
with talent or not,

51
00:05:59.025 --> 00:06:01.569 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
anyone could play well
after that much practice.

52
00:06:02.945 --> 00:06:05.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is the first time you told me that.

53
00:06:05.948 --> 00:06:08.367 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I never told anyone.

54
00:06:09.160 --> 00:06:11.079 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wanted people to think I was gifted.

55
00:06:20.004 --> 00:06:23.466 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You don’t have to wash me.
I took a bath just before I came here.

56
00:06:23.549 --> 00:06:28.304 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Old habits die hard.
But why are you so embarrassed?

57
00:06:28.387 --> 00:06:30.223 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m not embarrassed!

58
00:06:30.306 --> 00:06:31.224 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Like I’ve said many times,

59
00:06:31.307 --> 00:06:33.476 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m no longer on the pill,
so we’re not gonna do it in the bath.

60
00:06:33.559 --> 00:06:35.978 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I know, I know.
-Do you, really?

61
00:06:47.073 --> 00:06:49.617 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Ren…
-Hm?

62
00:06:49.700 --> 00:06:51.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That thing you said earlier. Is it true?

63
00:06:52.829 --> 00:06:54.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Which one?

64
00:06:54.539 --> 00:06:57.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Right now, I’m not about
to give up my pride,

65
00:06:58.417 --> 00:07:01.754 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
so I can’t live with you like we used to.

66
00:07:01.838 --> 00:07:07.593 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But it would be nice if we could maybe
meet like this from time to time.

67
00:07:07.677 --> 00:07:11.722 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hold each other and talk about each other.

68
00:07:12.890 --> 00:07:16.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And one day when we’re much older,

69
00:07:16.978 --> 00:07:20.231 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
when I no longer care
about pride and recognition,

70
00:07:20.314 --> 00:07:22.733 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
when I’ve grown tired of singing…

71
00:07:22.817 --> 00:07:26.571 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then can I return to that home too?

72
00:07:32.493 --> 00:07:35.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>That night, I had a dream.</i>

73
00:07:36.330 --> 00:07:38.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I don’t remember what I dreamt,</i>

74
00:07:39.000 --> 00:07:43.296 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>but in that dream, I was wrapped</i>
<i>in feelings of warmth and happiness.</i>

75
00:07:46.883 --> 00:07:51.971 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I woke up past noon and found Nana</i>
<i>there sleeping next to me.</i>

76
00:07:56.225 --> 00:07:58.394 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I wonder if it would be okay to ask her.</i>

77
00:07:58.478 --> 00:08:00.104 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I’m sure it would be okay.</i>

78
00:08:00.188 --> 00:08:03.107 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>She did say she’d tell me</i>
<i>anything if I ask.</i>

79
00:08:03.191 --> 00:08:04.317 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, Nana.

80
00:08:04.984 --> 00:08:06.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How’d it go with Ren?

81
00:08:08.988 --> 00:08:10.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I can’t answer anything you ask…

82
00:08:10.948 --> 00:08:13.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh? What? I don’t understand.

83
00:08:16.204 --> 00:08:17.538 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What I said was,

84
00:08:17.622 --> 00:08:19.957 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can’t answer anything
when I’m brushing my teeth!

85
00:08:20.875 --> 00:08:23.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Really, you’re not too good
at figuring things out, Hachiko.

86
00:08:23.878 --> 00:08:26.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, I shouldn’t expect much.
You’re a dog, after all.

87
00:08:26.923 --> 00:08:28.674 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Come on, Nana.</i>

88
00:08:28.758 --> 00:08:30.134 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thanks for the meal.

89
00:08:30.218 --> 00:08:32.178 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There’s more miso soup, so just ask.

90
00:08:32.261 --> 00:08:33.304 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you.

91
00:08:33.387 --> 00:08:35.681 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>She didn't answer my question.</i>

92
00:08:36.349 --> 00:08:37.558 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Liar!</i>

93
00:08:37.642 --> 00:08:39.435 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>And to think I was rooting for you so much</i>

94
00:08:39.519 --> 00:08:41.938 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>that I forgot to look at Takumi in person.</i>

95
00:08:42.021 --> 00:08:44.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>If I knew what was coming,</i>
<i>I would’ve only looked at Takumi.</i>

96
00:08:45.816 --> 00:08:47.276 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Takumi!</i>

97
00:08:47.360 --> 00:08:48.694 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Say, Hachiko…

98
00:08:49.487 --> 00:08:51.906 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I trust you, so I have a favor to ask.

99
00:08:51.989 --> 00:08:53.866 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>You trust me?</i>

100
00:08:53.950 --> 00:08:55.660 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sure. What can I do for you?

101
00:08:57.703 --> 00:09:00.623 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you do your job well,
I’ll give you a treat.

102
00:09:00.706 --> 00:09:03.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You did take good care of me
with this latest event after all.

103
00:09:03.209 --> 00:09:05.545 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What would you like? Beef jerky?

104
00:09:05.628 --> 00:09:06.796 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Takumi’s autograph!

105
00:09:06.879 --> 00:09:07.880 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Consider it done.

106
00:09:09.632 --> 00:09:10.883 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I will ask Ren for it.

107
00:09:12.843 --> 00:09:14.303 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right!

108
00:09:14.387 --> 00:09:16.347 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Does a simple autograph
please you that much?

109
00:09:16.430 --> 00:09:19.141 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s not that! You and Ren are
back together, aren’t you?

110
00:09:20.017 --> 00:09:22.645 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
W-- Well, I wouldn’t exactly… ah…

111
00:09:23.312 --> 00:09:26.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So what I’m asking,
since we don’t have a phone in our place…

112
00:09:26.607 --> 00:09:29.527 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, I do plan to buy a cell phone soon.

113
00:09:29.610 --> 00:09:31.153 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But in the meantime, should he need to,

114
00:09:31.237 --> 00:09:32.947 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was hoping Ren could call you
on your cell…

115
00:09:33.030 --> 00:09:36.826 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So you want me to take Ren’s call and
relay his messages to you, right, Nana?

116
00:09:36.909 --> 00:09:37.910 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s right.

117
00:09:37.994 --> 00:09:39.287 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’ll gladly do it.

118
00:09:39.370 --> 00:09:44.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Here’s Ren’s e-mail address,
so could you send him your address?

119
00:09:44.083 --> 00:09:45.835 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s great news, Nana.

120
00:09:45.918 --> 00:09:48.129 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-It’s not!
-Why not?

121
00:09:48.796 --> 00:09:52.800 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why does it have to end up like this?
This isn’t what I intended.

122
00:09:53.968 --> 00:09:55.261 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I went to wrap things up with him.

123
00:09:56.345 --> 00:09:58.889 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
My intentions were
to put an end to it all.

124
00:09:58.973 --> 00:10:00.766 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why did I get carried away?

125
00:10:02.143 --> 00:10:03.686 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That’s so lame.

126
00:10:03.769 --> 00:10:07.982 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>She said that while blushing</i>
<i>and curling up.</i>

127
00:10:08.065 --> 00:10:10.192 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I had never seen her look so cute.</i>

128
00:10:12.069 --> 00:10:17.575 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Geez… major adrenaline rush…</i>

129
00:10:18.326 --> 00:10:20.119 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I want happiness as soon as possible too.</i>

130
00:10:20.745 --> 00:10:21.912 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Or rather, a boyfriend.

131
00:10:21.996 --> 00:10:23.831 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then we’ll organize a party.

132
00:10:23.914 --> 00:10:28.336 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Not that way.
I want a love that’s meant to be.

133
00:10:28.419 --> 00:10:30.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, but now that you mention it,
a party might be good, too.

134
00:10:31.047 --> 00:10:32.923 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What the hell happened over there?

135
00:10:33.007 --> 00:10:35.259 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don’t ask me. I’m on a top secret mission.

136
00:10:35.343 --> 00:10:38.512 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Top secret? Finding a boyfriend?

137
00:10:39.138 --> 00:10:42.099 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But meeting someone at a party
could also be a love meant to be.

138
00:10:42.183 --> 00:10:43.976 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You don’t have to do that.

139
00:10:44.060 --> 00:10:46.270 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You’ve got plenty of men blooming
right in your own garden.

140
00:10:46.354 --> 00:10:47.813 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-My garden?
-Good point.

141
00:10:47.897 --> 00:10:50.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Take the band members
of your roommate’s band, for instance.

142
00:10:50.232 --> 00:10:53.653 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They seem like great guys for a punk band.

143
00:10:53.736 --> 00:10:56.197 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Isn’t there anyone from
the band that you like?

144
00:10:58.324 --> 00:11:00.368 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No! For one thing, Yasu belongs to Nana!

145
00:11:00.451 --> 00:11:01.911 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh? Yasu?

146
00:11:01.994 --> 00:11:03.829 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Those two are an item?

147
00:11:03.913 --> 00:11:05.414 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But actually they’re not.

148
00:11:05.498 --> 00:11:06.749 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now I’m confused.

149
00:11:06.832 --> 00:11:09.919 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, you see, Yasu’s really kind to Nana,

150
00:11:10.002 --> 00:11:11.420 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
so I thought there were an item.

151
00:11:11.504 --> 00:11:15.299 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Right. But Yasu’s like that
to anyone, right?

152
00:11:15.383 --> 00:11:17.259 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Like he’s reached a higher spirit,
like a monk.

153
00:11:17.343 --> 00:11:18.177 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He is bald after all.

154
00:11:19.136 --> 00:11:20.513 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>That’s right.</i>

155
00:11:21.055 --> 00:11:25.393 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Yasu’s kind to Nobu</i>
<i>and Shin and to me too.</i>

156
00:11:25.976 --> 00:11:28.354 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>It’s true. Yasu’s like that with everyone.</i>

157
00:11:28.437 --> 00:11:30.898 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>He’s like an elder brother to me.</i>

158
00:11:30.981 --> 00:11:33.484 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>In addition,</i>
<i>since Nana doesn’t have a family,</i>

159
00:11:33.567 --> 00:11:36.779 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Yasu must be thinking of Nana</i>
<i>as a real younger sister.</i>

160
00:11:36.862 --> 00:11:40.449 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>He must be feeling the need</i>
<i>to treat her better than a sister.</i>

161
00:11:41.033 --> 00:11:43.160 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I see. It’s all becoming clearer.</i>

162
00:11:43.244 --> 00:11:45.079 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Yasu’s a great guy.</i>

163
00:11:45.162 --> 00:11:46.288 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Right?
-Huh?

164
00:11:46.372 --> 00:11:47.873 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Listen when someone’s talking to you!

165
00:11:47.957 --> 00:11:51.043 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was saying, I wasn't expecting
that among the band members

166
00:11:51.127 --> 00:11:53.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
you'd bring up Yasu’s name.

167
00:11:53.963 --> 00:11:54.922 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh…

168
00:11:55.005 --> 00:11:57.883 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I thought you didn’t like guys like that,
with such a scary look.

169
00:11:57.967 --> 00:12:00.219 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mm-hmm. But Yasu’s different.

170
00:12:00.302 --> 00:12:01.512 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Once you get used to the skinhead,

171
00:12:01.595 --> 00:12:02.972 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you accept it as a charming part
of his character.

172
00:12:03.055 --> 00:12:07.935 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Also, I basically prefer calm,
composed guys who are older than me.

173
00:12:08.018 --> 00:12:09.895 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You know that, right, Jun-chan?

174
00:12:09.979 --> 00:12:11.772 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And on that note, Yasu’s very mature.

175
00:12:11.856 --> 00:12:13.899 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-In addition, he’s a lawyer.
-That’s not part of it.

176
00:12:13.983 --> 00:12:17.153 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Take away his looks and his job,
and he’s still a great guy inside.

177
00:12:17.236 --> 00:12:19.238 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What? A great guy inside?

178
00:12:19.947 --> 00:12:21.615 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I never imagined that

179
00:12:21.699 --> 00:12:23.159 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’d hear those words come out
of your mouth.

180
00:12:23.242 --> 00:12:24.452 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Great. Are you going for it?

181
00:12:24.535 --> 00:12:26.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Going where?

182
00:12:26.454 --> 00:12:28.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Wherever you need to.
Until you burn to ashes.

183
00:12:28.789 --> 00:12:31.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Junko, don’t lead her on.

184
00:12:31.083 --> 00:12:33.586 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We’re only talking about who
she’d prefer among those guys.

185
00:12:33.669 --> 00:12:35.880 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Th-- That’s right, Jun-chan!

186
00:12:37.256 --> 00:12:38.757 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She’s blushing. She’s blushing.

187
00:12:38.841 --> 00:12:40.134 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You seriously like him, by chance?

188
00:12:40.217 --> 00:12:44.388 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No way! I’ve never once thought
about Yasu and me getting together!

189
00:12:48.893 --> 00:12:50.019 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>That’s right.</i>

190
00:12:50.102 --> 00:12:52.396 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>Nothing can happen between Yasu and me.</i>

191
00:12:56.233 --> 00:12:58.152 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, Nana. You’re here.

192
00:12:58.777 --> 00:13:00.905 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
THUMP!

193
00:13:05.493 --> 00:13:07.036 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
G-- Good evening.

194
00:13:07.119 --> 00:13:09.288 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh? Where is everyone? Not here yet?

195
00:13:09.371 --> 00:13:11.999 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Nana’s here, but she went out
to buy cigarettes.

196
00:13:12.082 --> 00:13:13.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I see.

197
00:13:13.083 --> 00:13:15.377 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>What am I gonna do?</i>

198
00:13:15.461 --> 00:13:17.922 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>With Jun-chan bringing that subject up,</i>
<i>I can’t look at him the same way.</i>

199
00:13:18.005 --> 00:13:21.592 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>And it’s just us two here.</i>
<i>What are we gonna talk about?</i>

200
00:13:24.136 --> 00:13:27.473 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yasu. I brought this Trapnest pamphlet.
Wanna take a look?

201
00:13:27.556 --> 00:13:28.516 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah, thanks.

202
00:13:28.599 --> 00:13:30.476 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Did you hear from either Nana or Ren?

203
00:13:30.559 --> 00:13:32.686 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Those two are safely back together.

204
00:13:32.770 --> 00:13:35.147 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Really? I’m happy about that.

205
00:13:35.231 --> 00:13:37.608 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mm-hmm. I’m really happy about it.

206
00:13:37.691 --> 00:13:39.985 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was a bit down lately,
but now I’m feeling really good.

207
00:13:40.069 --> 00:13:43.531 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Huh? You were a bit down?
But you looked fine.

208
00:13:44.782 --> 00:13:46.158 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Was something troubling you?

209
00:13:52.289 --> 00:13:55.167 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ah, no. If you don’t wanna talk
about it, that’s okay.

210
00:13:56.669 --> 00:13:59.213 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My boyfriend cheated on me and dumped me.

211
00:14:06.220 --> 00:14:09.682 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He doesn’t realize what he lost.
What an idiot.

212
00:14:10.307 --> 00:14:13.852 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>But I was the one who said</i>
<i>I no longer wanted Shoji.</i>

213
00:14:14.687 --> 00:14:17.898 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The reason I used those foolish words,</i>
<i>"He dumped me,"</i>

214
00:14:17.982 --> 00:14:20.568 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>was because I wanted him</i>
<i>to be kind to me like this.</i>

215
00:14:21.485 --> 00:14:24.363 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>But I no longer want a kind man,</i>

216
00:14:24.446 --> 00:14:26.407 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>because it would hurt too much</i>
<i>when he betrays me.</i>

217
00:14:29.201 --> 00:14:32.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Still, Yasu is very trustworthy.</i>

218
00:14:32.496 --> 00:14:37.626 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>If I frequently see him like this,</i>
<i>I might really fall for him.</i>

219
00:14:38.210 --> 00:14:39.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Everyone’s late.

220
00:14:39.962 --> 00:14:41.755 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Would it be bad for me to fall</i>
<i>in love with him?</i>

221
00:14:41.839 --> 00:14:45.217 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where did Nana go to get cigarettes?

222
00:14:45.301 --> 00:14:46.969 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Should I not?</i>

223
00:14:47.052 --> 00:14:48.762 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Why don’t I ask?</i>

224
00:14:48.846 --> 00:14:51.223 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Say, Yasu, do you have a girlfriend?

225
00:14:51.932 --> 00:14:53.934 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Unfortunately, I’m not popular
with the women.

226
00:14:54.935 --> 00:14:56.937 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>What? But I like you a lot!</i>

227
00:14:57.605 --> 00:15:00.190 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hey, Yasu!
Ren sent me a reply to my email.

228
00:15:00.858 --> 00:15:03.152 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He has a break in his tour schedule
on the seventh and eighth of next month,

229
00:15:03.235 --> 00:15:04.695 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
so he’ll be returning here then.

230
00:15:04.778 --> 00:15:07.072 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He says if those days are fine with us,
we’ll have a mahjong tournament then.

231
00:15:07.156 --> 00:15:08.198 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is that so?

232
00:15:08.282 --> 00:15:10.242 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What’s that? I wanna join you!

233
00:15:10.326 --> 00:15:11.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh? You know how to play mahjong, Hachi?

234
00:15:12.077 --> 00:15:14.079 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I don’t, but…
-Good grief.

235
00:15:14.163 --> 00:15:15.414 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wanna meet Ren too!

236
00:15:15.497 --> 00:15:18.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What? But Hachiko,
I thought you were into Takumi.

237
00:15:18.459 --> 00:15:19.793 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You cheater!

238
00:15:19.877 --> 00:15:21.378 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don’t call me Hachiko.

239
00:15:21.462 --> 00:15:23.923 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Shin’s so not cute lately.</i>

240
00:15:24.006 --> 00:15:25.758 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where’s Nana?

241
00:15:25.841 --> 00:15:28.510 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh. She’s gone to Alaska
to buy cigarettes.

242
00:15:28.594 --> 00:15:29.595 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Alaska?

243
00:15:30.262 --> 00:15:32.848 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, is that Trapnest’s pamphlet?
Let me see it.

244
00:15:32.932 --> 00:15:35.184 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sure. Hachi brought it.

245
00:15:35.267 --> 00:15:36.268 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, I wanna see it too.

246
00:15:36.352 --> 00:15:38.896 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Hachi? Even Yasu’s calling me that now.</i>

247
00:15:40.272 --> 00:15:42.983 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Taking a close look like this,
Reira really is pretty.

248
00:15:43.067 --> 00:15:45.694 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh? Is she your type, Nobu?

249
00:15:45.778 --> 00:15:47.696 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’m not sure about type, but she’s great.

250
00:15:47.780 --> 00:15:49.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then next time let me introduce you

251
00:15:49.531 --> 00:15:50.783 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to a flight attendant
who looks just like her.

252
00:15:50.908 --> 00:15:53.369 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh? A flight attendant? Awesome!

253
00:15:53.452 --> 00:15:54.495 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She’s also really great at…

254
00:15:54.578 --> 00:15:55.746 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Shin!
-Don't want her!

255
00:15:55.829 --> 00:15:57.998 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-I’m not gonna become your brother!
-Brother?

256
00:15:58.082 --> 00:16:00.709 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, hi, Nana! You’re awfully late.

257
00:16:03.712 --> 00:16:05.089 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shin! How old are you?

258
00:16:05.172 --> 00:16:07.925 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Stop smoking, you brat.
Stop trying to act cool.

259
00:16:09.551 --> 00:16:11.720 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What’s gotten into you all
of a sudden, Nana?

260
00:16:11.804 --> 00:16:13.514 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You were letting him until now.

261
00:16:13.597 --> 00:16:15.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She’s scaring me! Save me, Hachi.

262
00:16:18.644 --> 00:16:19.687 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yasu!

263
00:16:19.770 --> 00:16:23.065 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yes, I get it. No smoking, right?
I’ll comply.

264
00:16:23.148 --> 00:16:24.566 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No smoking? Why?

265
00:16:24.650 --> 00:16:26.652 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
To increase my lung capacity.

266
00:16:26.735 --> 00:16:29.321 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where you that impressed by Reira’s voice?

267
00:16:29.405 --> 00:16:33.200 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That bitch has nothing to do with it!
I’ll kill you, baldie!

268
00:16:33.283 --> 00:16:37.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Since that evening,</i>
<i>Nana even began doing sit-ups.</i>

269
00:16:37.538 --> 00:16:39.873 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>So I decided to workout with her.</i>

270
00:16:41.166 --> 00:16:43.293 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why are you doing sit-ups too?

271
00:16:44.461 --> 00:16:47.131 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I wanna have a slim waist
for when I find a boyfriend.

272
00:16:47.214 --> 00:16:49.091 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I see. Then good luck with your efforts.

273
00:16:49.717 --> 00:16:53.095 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I wonder if Yasu will notice me</i>
<i>if I work hard at it.</i>

274
00:16:53.846 --> 00:16:55.222 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Maybe not.</i>

275
00:16:55.305 --> 00:16:59.101 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I somehow can’t picture Yasu</i>
<i>falling in love with me.</i>

276
00:16:59.184 --> 00:17:00.894 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nana-dear, make copies of this.

277
00:17:00.978 --> 00:17:04.273 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I don’t think he sees me as a woman.</i>

278
00:17:05.024 --> 00:17:08.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I get the same scent as that</i>
<i>of Mr. Mizukoshi.</i>

279
00:17:08.318 --> 00:17:11.947 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>My chances are slim.</i>
<i>Maybe I should give up.</i>

280
00:17:12.031 --> 00:17:15.576 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I’m no longer at that age where</i>
<i>I can be satisfied with one-sided love.</i>

281
00:17:15.659 --> 00:17:19.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Let’s look elsewhere, Nana-dear.</i>
<i>Perhaps a party is the way to go.</i>

282
00:17:19.538 --> 00:17:23.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Oh, somebody, hold me tight.</i>

283
00:17:26.336 --> 00:17:28.213 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>An e-mail.</i>

284
00:17:31.175 --> 00:17:34.053 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
FROM REN
A MESSAGE FOR NANA

285
00:17:35.012 --> 00:17:36.263 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>It’s come!</i>

286
00:17:38.932 --> 00:17:39.850 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>An email from Ren!</i>

287
00:17:39.933 --> 00:17:42.478 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Trapnest's Ren has sent</i>
<i>an email to my cell phone!</i>

288
00:17:42.561 --> 00:17:46.106 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I cannot believe something like this</i>
<i>is happening to a commoner like me!</i>

289
00:17:46.190 --> 00:17:49.193 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>It’s not addressed to me,</i>
<i>but can I read it?</i>

290
00:17:49.276 --> 00:17:50.986 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Even if I shouldn’t, I wanna read it.</i>

291
00:17:51.070 --> 00:17:51.987 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I’ll read it!</i>

292
00:17:52.071 --> 00:17:52.905 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A MESSAGE FOR NANA

293
00:17:52.988 --> 00:17:54.364 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
WE'RE PLAYING MAHJONG
AT NOBU'S PLACE ON THE NIGHT OF THE 7TH.

294
00:17:54.448 --> 00:17:55.741 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'M FREE DURING THE DAY,
CAN I COME BY YOUR PLACE?

295
00:17:55.824 --> 00:17:58.494 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, please come, darling.

296
00:17:58.577 --> 00:18:01.288 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That’s the reply I wrote.
So where’s my treat?

297
00:18:01.371 --> 00:18:03.999 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don’t reply on my behalf!
You’re not getting a treat.

298
00:18:04.083 --> 00:18:07.961 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I want Takumi’s autograph! Nana, you liar!

299
00:18:08.045 --> 00:18:10.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Listen, if Ren’s dropping by your place,

300
00:18:10.464 --> 00:18:12.466 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
why not have the mahjong tournament there?

301
00:18:12.549 --> 00:18:14.510 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
My place is too small
for a large number of people.

302
00:18:14.593 --> 00:18:15.552 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I agree!

303
00:18:15.636 --> 00:18:17.137 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That’s fine,
but we don’t have a mahjong table.

304
00:18:17.221 --> 00:18:20.182 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don’t either.
Just put a cloth over the table.

305
00:18:20.265 --> 00:18:22.976 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The table by the window?
But if we play sitting beside each other,

306
00:18:23.060 --> 00:18:24.978 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
it won’t be much of a match
with everything visible to others.

307
00:18:25.062 --> 00:18:27.022 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We’ll move the table and sit around it.

308
00:18:27.106 --> 00:18:28.649 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Don’t smoke!
-Oops!

309
00:18:28.732 --> 00:18:29.608 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I can’t wait!

310
00:18:29.691 --> 00:18:30.609 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
JUNE 7TH
MAHJONG TOURNAMENT

311
00:18:30.692 --> 00:18:32.611 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>I can't wait for the seventh!</i>

312
00:18:33.362 --> 00:18:37.241 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>Trapnest’s Ren is coming to our place.</i>
<i>Should I ask for his autograph?</i>

313
00:18:37.324 --> 00:18:39.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>If possible, we could have</i>
<i>a picture taken together?</i>

314
00:18:39.910 --> 00:18:41.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>What should I wear?</i>

315
00:18:41.370 --> 00:18:43.372 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>Should I buy that dress I wanted?</i>

316
00:18:43.455 --> 00:18:44.998 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>I should make an appointment</i>
<i>with the hairdresser too.</i>

317
00:18:45.082 --> 00:18:47.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>And I’ll prepare a bunch of food.</i>

318
00:18:47.376 --> 00:18:48.961 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>What should I make?</i>

319
00:18:49.044 --> 00:18:50.921 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>I should start preparing the night before.</i>

320
00:18:51.004 --> 00:18:52.589 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>I’ll get up early to clean up</i>

321
00:18:52.673 --> 00:18:55.092 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>and go to the flower shop,</i>
<i>so I can decorate the place with flowers…</i>

322
00:18:55.175 --> 00:18:58.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Chief, I’m expecting
an important guest tomorrow.

323
00:18:58.470 --> 00:18:59.972 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
May I take the day off from work?

324
00:19:00.055 --> 00:19:01.223 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course not!

325
00:19:01.306 --> 00:19:02.182 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
THURSDAY, JUNE 7TH
4:30 PM

326
00:19:02.266 --> 00:19:04.226 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>Thirty minutes before I get off work.</i>

327
00:19:04.309 --> 00:19:07.020 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>It’s about time people start arriving.</i>

328
00:19:07.104 --> 00:19:09.815 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Oh, I wanna hurry back home and see Ren.</i>

329
00:19:09.898 --> 00:19:11.859 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>That’s right. I should buy some paper</i>
<i>for an autograph on my way home.</i>

330
00:19:11.942 --> 00:19:14.736 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Please fire that girl, Chief!

331
00:19:14.820 --> 00:19:15.696 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hmm…

332
00:19:16.363 --> 00:19:18.574 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nana-dear, make copies of this. Huh?

333
00:19:19.283 --> 00:19:21.410 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ms. Komatsu has left for the day.

334
00:19:22.244 --> 00:19:23.120 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She left early?

335
00:19:23.203 --> 00:19:24.496 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We should fire her!

336
00:19:24.580 --> 00:19:25.581 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I guess you’re right.

337
00:19:27.082 --> 00:19:29.334 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You know, you’re really strong.

338
00:19:29.418 --> 00:19:30.627 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Could you be a little easier on me?

339
00:19:30.711 --> 00:19:32.129 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But I am.

340
00:19:32.212 --> 00:19:34.631 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shin, you’re being obnoxious.

341
00:19:34.715 --> 00:19:36.133 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I said, don’t smoke!

342
00:19:36.216 --> 00:19:39.761 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But Ren’s smoking.
So it’s okay for your own man to smoke.

343
00:19:39.845 --> 00:19:41.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You’re a typical woman after all, Nana.

344
00:19:41.722 --> 00:19:45.475 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don’t you know there is a law that
says it’s illegal for minors to smoke?

345
00:19:45.559 --> 00:19:48.103 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But you had been smoking
ever since you were a minor.

346
00:19:48.187 --> 00:19:50.772 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So what’s this about no smoking now?

347
00:19:50.856 --> 00:19:52.357 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Those around you are bothered by it.

348
00:19:52.441 --> 00:19:56.778 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don’t think it makes any difference.
There are many vocalists who smoke.

349
00:19:56.862 --> 00:19:58.780 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What you should do instead
is take some singing lessons.

350
00:19:58.864 --> 00:20:02.201 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Shut up! I don’t need you
giving me advice!

351
00:20:03.744 --> 00:20:05.871 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Oh, could that be Hachi?
-It could be Hachi.

352
00:20:05.954 --> 00:20:07.915 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Off you go.

353
00:20:08.749 --> 00:20:11.627 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, it’s not Hachi. It’s Nana.

354
00:20:11.710 --> 00:20:12.961 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You’re right.

355
00:20:13.503 --> 00:20:15.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>How should I greet him?</i>

356
00:20:15.380 --> 00:20:16.882 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>"Pleased to meet you. I’m Nana."</i>

357
00:20:16.965 --> 00:20:18.800 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>No. "I’m Komatsu."</i>

358
00:20:19.801 --> 00:20:22.930 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>"I’ve been a big fan</i>
<i>since Trapnest’s debut!"</i>

359
00:20:29.394 --> 00:20:30.938 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Welcome home, Nana.

360
00:20:41.240 --> 00:20:42.699 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Say, Nana…</i>

361
00:20:42.783 --> 00:20:45.452 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I made her cry. What should I do?

362
00:20:46.161 --> 00:20:49.581 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>That time, the reason my tears</i>
<i>suddenly came flowing out</i>

363
00:20:49.665 --> 00:20:51.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>was because I knew right away</i>

364
00:20:51.917 --> 00:20:56.171 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>that the dreamlike incident was</i>
<i>a treat you had arranged for me, Nana.</i>

365
00:20:57.756 --> 00:21:00.968 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I felt more love than being thanked</i>
<i>a million times.</i>

366
00:21:03.053 --> 00:21:05.055 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>And that made me really happy.</i>

